<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In the last few months or so, the SEC has laun=
ched a new and more aggressive crackdown on crypto than the 2017 version. A=
nd its approach is different.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are two main securities laws in the US, =
the =E2=80=9933 Act and the =E2=80=9934 Act. The =E2=80=9933 Act =E2=80=94=
=C2=A0the Securities Act of 1933 =E2=80=94=C2=A0regulates the <em>issuance=
=C2=A0</em>of securities: If you want to raise money for your business by s=
elling stocks or bonds, you have to register your sales with the Securities=
 and Exchange Commission and give buyers a prospectus with disclosure about=
 your business. The=C2=A0=E2=80=9934 Act =E2=80=94=C2=A0the Securities Exch=
ange Act of 1934 =E2=80=94=C2=A0regulates the=C2=A0<em>trading=C2=A0</em>of=
 securities: It has rules for stock exchanges and brokers, rules against fr=
aud in stock trading, rules for continuing disclosure by companies with pub=
licly traded stock.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The SEC=E2=80=99s 2017ish ICO crackdown was ve=
ry much a =E2=80=9933 Act crackdown: People were raising money by selling s=
cammy stock-like tokens, and the SEC shut down their scams, one at a=C2=A0t=
ime.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And one result of this approach is that Coinma=
rketcap.com lists 10,408 crypto tokens, and only a handful of them have bee=
n sued by the SEC for doing illegal securities offerings. Maybe that=E2=80=
=99s fine! Maybe the SEC=E2=80=99s crackdown on ICOs deterred 30,000 other,=
 scammier crypto projects from launching; maybe the 10,000 current crypto t=
okens are all pretty good and not scammy.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But one could imagine that the SEC disagrees. =
One could imagine that the SEC looks at the 10,000 existing crypto tokens a=
